From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 12:17:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 11/13] webimap transport: madmail HTTP mail access next to
 IMAP/SMTP

Adds a transport variant that speaks madmail's webimap/websmtp REST API
(github.com/themadorg/madmail, TDD 10-webimap) instead of IMAP/SMTP.
Browsers can talk to it directly over fetch() with CORS, so wasm builds
need no WebSocket-TCP bridge for such accounts.

- net/http: new portable request(context, method, url, headers, body,
  timeout, follow_redirects) -> (status, Response) on both targets.
  Native: hyper via get_http_sender wrapped in tokio::time::timeout
  (hyper never follows redirects, so the flag is a no-op there). wasm:
  the existing fetch() plumbing gains custom headers, an
  AbortController-backed timeout and RequestRedirect::Error for
  follow_redirects=false so credential headers are never re-sent to a
  redirect target; the read_url*/post_* wrappers now route through it
  with a 60s default timeout.
- login_param/transport: new `webimap: bool` on EnteredLoginParam and
  ConfiguredLoginParam(-Json), serde-defaulted so both JSON DB columns
  and sync messages stay compatible without a migration.
- src/webimap.rs: WebimapClient (X-Email/X-Password auth), verify() via
  GET /webimap/mailboxes, smtp_send() via POST /webimap/send with the
  same SendResult semantics as the SMTP path, and webimap_loop() which
  long-polls GET /webimap/messages?since_uid=0&wait=60, feeds each
  message through receive_imf and deletes it from the server. No UID
  persistence: deletion after processing plus Message-ID dedup covers
  restarts. Base URL is https://host[:port]; plain http only for
  localhost as a mock-server test hatch.
- scheduler: webimap transports spawn webimap_loop instead of
  inbox_loop, reusing ImapConnectionState/-Handlers wholesale.
- smtp: smtp_send() routes webimap transports to webimap::smtp_send()
  (single choke point for messages, MDNs, sync, status updates);
  connect_configured() is a no-op for webimap so the pre-connect in
  send_msg_to_smtp does not dial a nonexistent SMTP server.
- configure: webimap-shaped ConfiguredLoginParam is derived directly
  from the entered params (host defaults to the addr domain) and
  verified with one authenticated HTTP request; is_chatmail=1 since
  madmail enforces PGP-only like chatmail.
- qr: new `webimapaccount:host[:port]` scheme decoding into
  Qr::Account { webimap: true }; account creation via POST /new reusing
  CreateAccountSuccessResponse. dc_lot/jsonrpc mirrors updated
  (QrObject::Account and EnteredLoginParam gain the webimap field).

